.TH JTCORE "1" "April 2026" "jtcore manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtcore \- Compile one JT core
.SH DESCRIPTION
JTCORE compilation tool. (c) Jose Tejada 2019\-2023, @topapate
usage: jtcore <corename> [options]
.IP
jtcore compiles only one core at a time. To compile many cores at once
use jtupdate.
.IP
Macro definition
\fB\-\-def\fR | \fB\-d\fR   Defines a verilog macro. Macros are removed from qsf file after
.IP
compilation.
Useful macros:
.TP
NOSOUND
the core is compiled without sound (faster)
.TP
MISTER_VIDEO_MIXER
uses the Mr video modules
.TP
JTFRAME_SCAN2X
uses simple scan doubler from JTFRAME
.IP
MISTER_DEBUG_NOHDMI skips MiSTer HDMI related logic. Speeds up compilation.
.HP
\fB\-\-undef\fR | \fB\-u\fR Undefines a macro
.IP
Target selection
\fB\-mist\fR       compiles the MiST version. This is the default
\fB\-mister\fR     compiles the MiSTer version
\fB\-sidi\fR       compiles the SIDI version. This uses MiST's folders and settings but different pinout
\fB\-neptuno\fR    compiles the NeptUNO version
\fB\-mc2\fR        compiles the MultiCore2  version
\fB\-mcp\fR        compiles the MultiCore2+ version
\fB\-pocket\fR     compiles the PocketFPGA version
\fB\-sockit\fR     compiles the Arrow SoCKit version
\fB\-de1soc\fR     compiles the Terasic DE1\-SoC version
\fB\-de10std\fR    compiles the Terasic DE10\-Standard version
\fB\-folder\fR     any folder present in \fI\,/home/jtejada/jtcores/modules/jtframe/target/folder\/\fP can be used as the target
.IP
General options
.TP
\fB\-\-corestamp\fR
Sets the date string attached to the RBF file name. Defaults to today
.TP
\fB\-\-credits\fR
Defines NOSOUND, MISTER_DEBUG_NOHDMI and NOMAIN. Sets MiSTer as target.
.TP
\fB\-mrq\fR
Compiles MiSTer with no HDMI nor logo but with sound
.TP
\fB\-\-mrpasswd\fR
Sets the SSH pasword to use on MiSTer
.TP
\fB\-\-nodbg\fR
Defines JTFRAME_RELEASE
.TP
\fB\-\-nosta\fR
skips the STA check and marks as PASS compilations with timing problems
.TP
\fB\-\-nolinter\fR
Do not run the verilator linter
.TP
\fB\-\-program\fR | \fB\-p\fR
Programs the FPGA via JTAG
.TP
\fB\-\-quick\fR |\-q
Quick compilation. Defines NOSOUND and JTFRAME_OSD_NOLOGO
Disables JTFRAME_CREDITS and HQ2X.
.TP
\fB\-qs\fR
Same as \fB\-q\fR but with sound.
.HP
\fB\-\-quicker\fR | \fB\-qq\fR Same as \fB\-q\fR but it also disabled HDMI output and sets MiSTer as target
.TP
\fB\-\-sd\fR [setname]
Copy to sd card, optional setname (uses jtbin2sd)
.TP
\fB\-\-seed\fR
Sets random seed for compilation
.TP
\fB\-\-sim\fR
Prepares Quartus simulation
.TP
\fB\-\-skip\fR | \fB\-s\fR
skips the compilation but executes the rest of the commands
.TP
\fB\-\-showmacros\fR
Shows the macros used for compilation and exits
.TP
\fB\-\-target\fR | \fB\-t\fR <target>
Specifies the target platform
.TP
\fB\-\-verbose\fR | \fB\-v\fR
verbose
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Shows the core version. Use "jtmerge \fB\-v\fR" to see the JTFRAME version
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Displays this message
